> [!WARNING]
> Blizzard doesn't let you click "Edit mode" to switch profile until you leave the tutorial area. Things will look a little off until they let you click this button, and other aspects of the UI are disabled in the starter area. In the meantime, It can be a good idea to temporarily disable the addon 'MouseOverActionBars' until you finish Exile’s reach.

---

## Step 1: Backing Up

> [!NOTE]
> This is a one time transition step that won't have to be repeated in the future. If you're fresh installing WoW, you can skip it.

1. Back up your existing WTF folder somewhere safe.

2. Then, if you played in SL, I'd strongly suggest deleting the Interface and WTF folders entirely for a fresh start.

	The Config.wtf file in `/WTF` contains settings specific to your PC that should probably be preserved; graphics settings and such. You can launch the game once and then replace the generated Config.WTF with your old one which you backed up.
---

## Step 2: Files


1. Determine your Account#/Name. It's the name of your account folder in `/WTF`. Mine is 316686#1, for example. If you don't have one, launch the game, close, and it will have generated the folder.

2. Copy the contents of the `Install Files` folder to your `World of Warcraft/_retail_` folder.

3. Delete your account# folder and rename the `NNNNNN#N` folder in `/WTF/Account` to your account#.

4. At this point, replace the Config.WTF if you saved it.

5. You can now launch the game for reals

---

## Step 3: Configuration

### `Escape -> Edit Mode`
Import the string from [[EditModeString\|EditModeString]] (profile has to be applied per spec, but should only need to be imported to your account once.)

### `Escape -> Options -> Action Bars`
Enable additional Actionbars as desired (only 1-4 are sensibly placed right now.)

### `/tmw options -> General`
![Pasted image 20221029060746.png](data:image/png;base64,)
(Bottom Right)
Then:
![Pasted image 20221029060810.png](data:image/png;base64,)
(Top Left)
Change profile in the top left to `FahUI<ClassHere>`

> [!note]
> TMW is currently configured to not display anything below level 10. If you see nothing at these levels, it’s fine.

### `Escape -> Options -> Addons(tab at top) -> Clique -> General Options`
Change profile to `FahUI<ClassHere>` 

### `/kb to do your keybindings. recommend checking “Character specific”`

### `AdvancedInterfaceOptions -> Cvar Browser → type in “SpellQueueWindow”`
This is a check everybody should make once and adjust to their liking; the default is 400 which is almost certainly too high, and most older recommendations told you to set it too low. It’s going to depend on feel but something between 125 and 250 is probably best. Do take into account your average latency. Here’s an [explanation](http://thedefiantguild.com/forums/discussion/15431.html) of this value.

### Give the UI a /reload

# You should be good to go from here if you're lazzy or just want to get playing.


## These keybinds are pre-configured as global bindings in the Clique profile. They allow you to control or (if something goes wrong) repair various aspects of the TMW layout.

|Function   | Keybind   |
|------- | ----  |
|Classic Layout (Default) | Numpad_Minus|
|Merged Layout | Numpad_Plus|
|Use only one Main TMW bar (Default) | Numpad_Divide|
|Use Two TMW Main bars | Numpad_Multiply|

## If you want an understanding of the difference between layouts, read the [[Layouts\|Layouts]] page. If you want to understand the existing UI elements, check out [[Addons\|Addons]]. If you want to expand the UI, check out [[Optional Addons\|Optional Addons]]. Unique, class specific UI elements that might warrant further explanation and useful macros are listed on respective class pages in the “C” folder, like [[C/Paladin\|C/Paladin]]. Find information on how to go about updating your addons on [[Update\|Update]].

## Optional Step: Customization

### Font
If you'd like to use a different font, (first back up) then overwrite the `FRIZQT__.ttf` file in `_retail_/Fonts` with a TTF of your choice. It doesn't matter what the font is, it has to be named that. The installed font is Expressway. If you want to return to the WoW default (Friz Quadrata TT) just delete the ttf in this folder.


### Keybind text on TMW
Say you want to use mouseover action bars and just rely on TMW for your abilities, but there's still just a few bindings you tend to forget. Here's how to add keybind text to a TMW icon:

### `/tmw`
Observe the buckets of spell icons located near the top right of the screen
![Pasted image 20221023002804.png](data:image/png;base64,)

Here's the process for making the Dragonrage ability display my keybind text for it:

1. Right click on the icon, bringing up the TMW config for the ability.
2.  In the bottom right, enter the desired keybind in the "1." field. My dragonrage is bound to shift+E, so I'll enter "SE".
 ![Pasted image 20221023003121.png](data:image/png;base64,)
3.  ![Pasted image 20221023003139.png](data:image/png;base64,)

> [!Note]
> It's pointless to add keybind text to **utility** spells in the "Classic" [layout](Layouts), because they're only shown when they're on cooldown anyway. Do it in the "Merged" [layout](Layouts) if that's your thing.

### This should only be used sparingly for binds you're at risk of forgetting. They'll also be overwritten if I need to update the TMW profiles in the future. If you tend to forget all of your keybinds without having them readily available, I recommend disabling TMW and mouseover action bars, or just using a different UI setup altogether.
